# ── Native (Capacitor / Android) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Defense in depth at the ROOT: android/ has its own .gitignore, but nested
# ignore files vanish from disk when you switch to a branch that predates them —
# which is exactly how 900+ build artifacts once got swept into a commit by a
# `git add -A`. Root-level rules survive every branch switch.
android/app/build/
android/build/
android/.gradle/
android/local.properties
# Regenerated by `npx cap sync android` — never hand-edited, never committed.
android/app/src/main/assets/public/
android/app/src/main/assets/capacitor.config.json
android/app/src/main/assets/capacitor.plugins.json
android/app/src/main/res/xml/config.xml
android/capacitor-cordova-android-plugins/
# Future iOS shell (same reasoning).
ios/App/build/
ios/App/Pods/
ios/DerivedData/
# Retired Flutter app (removed 2026-07-11, source archived at tag
# archive/flutter-mobile). An IDE with the old project still open regenerates
# .dart_tool/build/.idea cruft under mobile/; ignore the whole tree so a stray
# `git add -A` can never re-commit it. Restore the source with:
#   git checkout archive/flutter-mobile -- mobile/
/mobile/

# Packaged binaries never belong in git.
*.apk
*.aab
*.ipa

# ── Signing material & service credentials (SECURITY: never commit) ──────────
*.keystore
*.jks
*.p12
*.pem
*.mobileprovision
key.properties
google-services.json
GoogleService-Info.plist

# ── Local tooling / caches ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tsbuildinfo
.eslintcache
coverage/
Thumbs.db
.claude/settings.local.json
.serena/cache/
